title: Black Beauty
description: Black Beauty is a classic adventure tale for children to read and enjoy.

title: Planet Omar: Accidental Trouble Magnet by Zanib Mian
description: The first book in the exciting #OwnVoices middle-grade debut starring a Muslim boy with a huge imagination--now in paperback! Welcome to the imaginative brain of Omar! Omar and his family have just moved, and he is NOT excited about starting at a new school.

title: The Flower Fairies by Emily Rodda
description: Enter the Realm of delight....Jessie is a real hero in the Realm now -- her fast thinking saved the land from disaster. She even gets to dance in midair with the beautiful flower fairies.Now the Realm needs her again: the griffins that guard the treasure house are out of control, and then the flower fairies follow Jessie out of the Realm. Can she protect them from the dangers of her own world?

title: The Worst Witch
description: The Worst Witch is a series of children's books written and illustrated by Jill Murphy. The series are primarily about a girl who attends a witch school and fantasy stories, with eight books published

title: The Witches - Roald Dahl
description: The Witches is a British children's dark fantasy novel by the British writer Roald Dahl. The story is set partly in Norway and partly in England, and features the experiences of a young English boy and his Norwegian grandmother in a world where child-hating societies of witches secretly exist in every country.

title: The King and the Gifts of Gold by Georg Dreissig
description: There was once a powerful king so rich that he was known as the King of Gold. The king took his riches for granted until one day a wondrous star appeared and he was inspired to follow it into the desert.

title: Daisy and the Trouble with Giants
description: Daisy has decided she wants to meet a real giant! If Daisy met a real giant he'd pick Daisy up and put her on his shoulder and they'd have giant adventures! They'd eat sweets as big as tractor tires, and if she got thirsty, they'd have giant lemonades out of giant straws. It would be sooooo gooood!

title: THE CHARM BRACELET by Emily Rodda
description: Jessie goes to stay with her grandmother in her rambling old house and discovers an amazing secret - a magical door in her grandmother's garden opens into a real fairy world.

title: Paddington Races Ahead
description: Paddington has warmed the hearts of generations of readers with his earnest good intentions and humorous misadventures. This brand-new edition of the classic novel contains the original text by Michael Bond and illustrations by Peggy Fortnum and R.W. Alley.

title: The Night Bus Hero by Rauf, Onjali Q.
description: What does it take to turn a bully into a hero? Empathy and the power of forgiveness take center stage in this poignant novel by the award-winning author of The Boy at the Back of the Class.Getting in trouble is what Hector does best. He knows that not much is expected of him.

title: A Muslim Boy's Guide to Life's Big Changes
description: A Muslim Boy's Guide to Life's Big Changes gives 'brotherly' advice on life in general from Islam and friends, school and home life through to the physical changes you will experience from the age of 11 onwards as you reach puberty. Recommended for ages 10-15

title: Trapped in a Video Game
description: After Full Blast, Jesse Rigsby and his friend Eric has sworn off video games. But when Jesse is offered the chance to save his friend Mark, of course he says, 'Yes.' Problem is, Jesse is invisible now, sucked into the world of Go Wild?a?Pok?mon Go?style mobile game.

title: The Adventures of Captain Underpants -The Sixth
description: Captain Underpants is an illustrated children's novel series by American author and illustrator David Pilkey.

title: The Adventures of Captain Underpants -The Eighth
description: Captain Underpants is an illustrated children's novel series by American author and illustrator David Pilkey.

title: The Adventures of Captain Underpants -The First
description: Captain Underpants is an illustrated children's novel series by American author and illustrator David Pilkey.

title: Tom Swift Young Inventor - The Robot Olympics
description: om's been training his entry, SwiftBot, for the upcoming Robot Olympics -- a major event being sponsored by the White House's Office of Science and Technology. Teenage inventors from around the country will be bringing their homemade robots to compete in a series of athletic competitions.

title: A Christmas for Bear by Bonny Becker
description: Bear?s understated Christmas celebration has Mouse feeling a bit anxious in this humorous and heart-warming story featuring the unlikely, loveable pair.Features an audio read-along!

title: Soccer Squad: Glory!  by Bali Rai
description: Dal, Chris, Abs and Jason have made the squad for the local youth club under-lls football team. And after their first match (not?as successful as they'd have liked), they are determined to prove that they've got what it takes to be winners.

title: Soccer Squad: Starring Eleven!  by Bali Rai
description: Dal, Chris, Abs and Jason have made the squad for the local youth club under-lls football team. And after their first match (not?as successful as they'd have liked), they are determined to prove that they've got what it takes to be winners.

title: Soccer Squad: Missing!  by Bali Rai
description: Dal, Chris, Abs and Jason have made the squad for the local youth club under-lls football team. And after their first match (not?as successful as they'd have liked), they are determined to prove that they've got what it takes to be winners.The Rushton Reds have lost their first two matches. Missed chances, missed goals - even missed penalties! Their coaches say they need to play more as a team - and they have an idea for a great team-building day. But will it help the Reds hit the back of the net?

title: Soccer Squad: Stars!  by Bali Rai
description: Dal, Chris, Abs and Jason have made the squad for the local youth club under-11s football team. And after their first match (not as successful as they'd have liked), they are determined to prove that they've got what it takes to be winners.Jason, Dal, Abs and Chris are about to be famous! A TV documentary is being made about their team and everyone wants the chance to shine in front of the cameras. But what is more important - looking like a star, or playing well as part of the team? When Abs takes his posing a bit too far, is he getting too big for his boots?

title: The Tail of Emily Windsnap
description: Emily Windsnap is a series of children's fantasy novels written by British author Liz Kessler, inaugurated by The Tail of Emily Windsnap in 2003 and continuing as of 2020. It is illustrated primarily by Sarah Gibb and published by Orion Children's Books in Britain, and Candlewick Press in America.

title: The Royal Rabbits of London - Santa Montefiore
description: 'Packed with fun, fantasy and the sort of adventure guaranteed to have sticky little fingers hungrily turning the pages' The Mail on Sunday Life is an adventure. Anything in the world is possible - by will and by luck, with a moist carrot, a wet nose and a slice of mad courage!

title: The Golden Lily by Richelle Mead
description: The Golden Lily is a 2012 urban fantasy young adult novel by New York Times bestselling author Richelle Mead and is the second novel of the Bloodlines series. The book follows several teenaged students as they deal with forbidden romances, the Strigoi, and the supernatural in general.

title: The Scottish Prisioner
description: The Scottish Prisoner?is part of her spinoff series about Lord John Grey, but the story focuses on Jamie during a heartbreaking stage of his life.

title: Matter by Iain M. Banks
description: Matter?is a science?fiction novel?from Iain M. Banks set in his Culture universe.

title: Insurrection by Robyn Young
description: Insurrection tells the story of Robert from his youth in a safe, stable Scotland, through the period of disaster following the death of Alexander.

title: Last Sacrifice by Richelle Mead
description: Last Sacrifice is the sixth book in the #1 New York Times bestselling series, Vampire Academy by Richelle Mead. It is the last book in the original storyline, but Mead will continue writing more Vampire Academy books in a spinoff series.

title: Human Traces by Sebastian Faulks
description: Human Traces is a 2005 novel by Sebastian Faulks, best known as the British author of Birdsong and Charlotte Gray. The novel took Faulks five years to write. It tells of two friends who set up a pioneering asylum in 19th-century Austria, in tandem with the evolution of psychiatry and the start of the First World War.

title: Days of Blood & Starlight by Laini Taylor
description: Days of Blood and Starlight is a young adult fantasy novel written by Laini Taylor. It was published in November 2012 by Hachette Book Group, an imprint of Little, Brown and Company. The book is the second in a trilogy, preceded by Daughter of Smoke and Bone and followed by Dreams of Gods and Monsters.

title: Blood Promise by Richelle Mead
description: Blood Promise?is the fourth book in the?Vampire Academy?series by?Richelle Mead.[1]?Previously in the series, the main character, Rose, and her true love Dimitri made a pact that if either of them were turned into?strigoi, the other would kill them rather than let them roam as an evil vampire.?Blood Promise?follows Rose's emotional struggle as she travels to Russia to hunt down Dimitri and fulfill this promise.

title: Assassin's Creed Forsaken by Oliver Bowden
description: Assassin's Creed: Forsaken is a novel written by Oliver Bowden, which was released on 4 December 2012. The novel is presented as the journal of Haytham Kenway, showing the story of how he became a Templar and the events of Assassin's Creed III from his perspective. The date of release was also the date that Haytham was born.

title: 2312 A novel by KIM Stanley Robinson
description: 2312 is a hard science fiction novel by American writer Kim Stanley Robinson, published in 2012. It is set in the year 2312 when society has spread out across the Solar System. The novel won the 2013 Nebula Award for Best Novel.
